One of the main challenges faced during this assignment was balancing the different needs of stakeholders. For example, students require a simple and fast system, while IT staff focus on system performance and security.

Another challenge was ensuring that functional requirements align with stakeholder concerns, also keeping the system simple enough for development.

Trade-offs had to be made between usability and security, as adding more security features can sometimes make the system harder to use.

Overall, the process helped improve understanding of requirement engineering and stakeholder analysis.
